 ## Issues Found
-1. [CRITICAL] Fix 4 excludes cancelled orders from `selfTotal` but still renders cancelled self orders. Prompt lines 945-947 filter `selfTotal` with `isCancelledOrder(o)`, then lines 971-1004 iterate `myOrdersInSession.map(...)` without the same filter. On a mixed session, the new self-card total/header will exclude cancelled orders while the visible rows still include them, which breaks the active-orders-only intent from Fix 1 and makes the card internally inconsistent. PROMPT FIX: introduce `const activeMyOrdersInSession = myOrdersInSession.filter((o) => !isCancelledOrder(o));`, use it for both `selfTotal` and the render loop, and update the AC to say cancelled self orders are hidden in the self-block.
-2. [MEDIUM] Fix 3 contains contradictory `currentTableKey` guidance. The prose at lines 706-714 and the inline comment at line 773 still describe `name || code`, but the actual snippet at lines 721-726 and the AC at line 881 require `code || name`. This conflict can easily produce a wrong or half-updated implementation. PROMPT FIX: normalize every occurrence to `currentTable?.code || currentTable?.name || null` and remove the stale `name || code` wording/comments.
-3. [MEDIUM] Fix 3 hook-order guidance is still structurally ambiguous. The warning at lines 675-679 correctly says `useEffect` must be inserted before the early return, but the document still presents Step 3.4 before Step 3.3. An implementer following the document top-to-bottom can still place the conditional return first and create a Rules-of-Hooks regression. PROMPT FIX: physically reorder the sections so Step 3.3 appears before Step 3.4 in the prompt, then remove the meta-explanation about document order vs code order.
-4. [MEDIUM] Fix 2 does not fully resolve how submitted orders should be labeled in SECTION 5 and the new self-block rows. R1 says `'submitted'` should become `⏳ Ожидает`, but the replacement snippets at lines 606-639 and 971-1001 still derive row status text from `getSafeStatus(stageInfo)`. In the current source, `getSafeStatus(null)` returns `В работе` (`CartView.jsx:309-317`), so a submitted order can render both an `⏳ Ожидает` badge and a `⏳ В работе` label at the same time. PROMPT FIX: either instruct the implementer to override the row label for pending orders (or update `getSafeStatus`) or explicitly state that the double-label is intentional.
-5. [LOW] Fix 4 relies on `getGuestLabelById(myGuestId)` for the self-card title even though the current helper falls back through `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.indexOf(gid)` and returns `Гость ?` for IDs not present in `sessionGuests` (`CartView.jsx:533-539`). The prompt only covers the happy path where the guest exists in `sessionGuests`. PROMPT FIX: use a dedicated self-label helper based on `currentGuest`/`guestDisplay`, or document that `sessionGuests` membership is a prerequisite for the desired label.
+1. [MEDIUM] Fix 3 verification still depends on `submittedTableTotal` after Fix 1 removes it — Fix 3’s pre-review grep expects `sessionOrders` evidence at the `submittedTableTotal` block (task lines 815-817), but Fix 1 Step 1.3 explicitly deletes that block (lines 427-434). In the real execution order, a reviewer who reaches Fix 3 after applying Fix 1/2 can no longer reproduce the expected hits at former lines 526/528, which makes the verification stale and can trigger false hesitation or a false STOP. PROMPT FIX: move this verification into an explicit baseline/pre-Fix-1 preparation step, or rewrite it to rely only on anchors that survive Fix 1 (`sessionOrders` prop at line 59 plus the `sessionOrders.length > 0` checks at lines 848/871).
+2. [MEDIUM] Fix 4 acceptance overstates the self-label fallback — The prompt requires the self card title to read `«Вы (Гость N)»` via `getGuestLabelById(myGuestId)` (task lines 1153-1155), but the actual helper falls back through `otherGuestIdsFromOrders.indexOf(gid)` in [CartView.jsx](/abs/path/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:533). Because `myGuestId` is explicitly excluded from `otherGuestIdsFromOrders` ([CartView.jsx](/abs/path/C:/Users/ASUS/Dev/Menu AI Cowork/menuapp-code-review/pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:510)), the fallback for a self guest missing from `sessionGuests` becomes `Гость ?`, not `Гость N`. This is documented only in the changelog, not in the live Fix 4 instructions, so a correct implementation can still fail review. PROMPT FIX: add an explicit Fix 4 note/AC that `Гость ?` is acceptable in this edge case, or specify a dedicated self-label fallback that does not depend on `otherGuestIdsFromOrders`.
+3. [LOW] Fix 3 relies on an off-file runtime contract without a concrete source reference — The section states that `closeSession()` atomically flips all active table orders to `status: 'closed'` and cites “S286 Б1” and commit `35726f1` (task lines 806-808), but it does not give the implementer a readable path/file to verify that contract from the repository. Since the review instructions tell the executor to self-read the target source file, this creates a context gap around the most important predicate in `tableIsClosed`. PROMPT FIX: link the exact file/path that implements `closeSession()` or downgrade the statement to an assumption plus a required runtime verification note.
+4. [LOW] One frozen-UX verification is too weak to catch the regression it is meant to prevent — The post-fix check `grep -a -n "formatPrice" ... | grep -iE "pending|in_progress|served"` (task lines 1258-1260) only catches same-line matches. A price inserted into a bucket header via multiline JSX, an intermediate variable, or a nearby line would slip through while still violating the spec. PROMPT FIX: require a targeted read of the bucket-header block around the `bucketOrder.map()` header render, or use a context grep around `bucketDisplayNames[key]` and inspect the surrounding lines instead of relying on same-line text matching.
 
